Text.Value: What are ya... what are ya doin'?
Leave.
A tribe like yours must have plenty of treasure. Where's it hiding?
Will do.
Then hurry up an' do it. My tribe ain't as friendly as I am.
Never break a promise unless there's somefin' in it for me.
No, I'll talk, I'll talk!
I guess yer right - I'm worgmeat either way.
Those teeth. Those 'orrible teeth.
Ain't sure why ya killed yer own to protect me. Don't care, neither.
I won't bother ya any more. I swear.
No point turnin' on yer own if yer just gonna give 'em a little tap.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking - just watched you attack allies to save her but let them live

Text.Value: Attack.
O' course, I'll prob'ly be a rat's breakfast myself if I don't tell this one something.

EditorData.VFXTags: Player reading the mind of Sazza

Text.Value: I ain't sayin' nuffin' else. They'll kill me an' kill me slow.
Gratitude doesn't help me. Tell me about that priestess.
In a moment. Stay here and keep out of the way.
I know plenty of deities, but the Absolute's a new god to me.
The Absolute? I've read nothing of this god in my studies.
Another god? I swear Toril has more deities than there are stars in the sky.
I've never heard of this god of yours.
Get me outta here, and I'll take you to meet her and the rest of my tribe.
With the way things are going, I could use a blessing.
'Course I do. We all do.
Leave.
Sorry, follow me.
They're gonna burn this pretty place for the glory of the Absolute and 'ang ya by yer guts.
All right. You've captured my interest.
We'll be heroes, blessed by Priestess Gut in the name of the Absolute.
An all-powerful goddess that couldn't get you out of a cage?
'Ello again. Commander's waitin' to meet ya. Don't be shy.
I've saved your hide twice now. You owe me.
Who is this god you keep mentioning?
You keep mentioning this god, but I've never seen them in my studies.
Another god? I swear, Toril has more deities than there are stars in the sky.
This god of yours is new to me.
Gonna go tell the commander 'bout you. All nice things, 'course.
Unless... unless ya listen to me. I can save ya.
We're moving. Keep close to me.
You won't believe what you can do once you've got the blessin' of the Absolute.
Oh, we like it when people run - makes 'em taste sweeter when ya catch 'em.
Ah, thought I was never gonna get outta there.
Yeah. Take me back to the tribe, and we'll tell the boss all about this pretty little place so she can burn it to the ground.
I tell ya anything, and my life ain't worth a rat's breakfast.
You're not mates with the tiefs, are you? You need to get back to your own people before you go soft.
If she's as cruel as you say, she'll crush your tribe under her heel.
Read her mind.
No one deserves to be locked up like that.
Why'd ya open my cage? Think we're gonna be friends?
Leave.
Yer a long way from home, ain't ya, underdwarf?
I'll do a lot worse than that cage if you don't make this worth my while.
I'll introduce ya to my whole tribe and put in a good word for ya - see ya at the camp.

EditorData.NodeContext: slightly menacing; she's going to break her promise

Text.Value: What could a tribe of goblins possibly offer me?
I met your friend. Ready to go?
Let me go. I'll sneak off and become a hermit - won't cause trouble for nobody.

EditorData.NodeContext: pleading; just survived an attempted execution

Text.Value: Things are changin'. The Absolute's bringin' us all together - goblins, drow, duergar, gnolls.
Ready to go meet my tribe? Just say the word.

EditorData.logicalname: Door open, PC promised to free her

Text.Value: Yeah, 'ow many were there? Four?
Dunno. I don't repay 'em, as a rule.
Is that it? Can I go?
Dunno - never repaid anything. But you been square with me, true.
It ain't safe here. Hurry back.
'Appily. Lead the way.
You're in trouble no matter what. You may as well talk.
Don't believe you. You ain't got enough scars to be one of her playthings.
Don't believe you. There's something a bit soft about you.
The Absolute is gold from the sky, She is. The blessin' in the storm an' the storm itself.
Ah, the 'Absolute'. Is this the deity you're bowing to?
Leave.
Stop following me so closely.
Unless... unless ya listen to me. I can save ya.
Who is this Absolute?
Who's your 'boss lady'?
We're burnin' Her name across the face o' the world, we are.
Didn't expect to see a drow in here. Did the boss lady send you to rescue me?
I ain't surprised. Tell you wot.
Think my tribe'll care? They'll peel yer face off and nail it to a wall!
Just lemme go.
An' that's all I know, I swear.
You made me a promise, remember?
Well, maybe She sent ya to 'elp me. An' ya will, if ya wanna save yer skin.
I've made some strange alliances, but... is she really your 'mate'?
What do ya wanna know?
You want it? It's yours! It's all yours!
Sure fing. I'll 'ang back a little.
Attack.
Uh... sure they don't.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: *She stares at the player like they're insane.*

Text.Value: Yes, she sent me. Ready to get out of here?
TELL ME, OR YOU'LL BE MY BREAKFAST.
Tell me, or you'll be my breakfast.
'Appily. Lead the way.
We got more than ya can 'andle. We're gonna tear yer gate down an' peel yer skins off.
I saw Dror Ragzlin stash some stuff behind the waterfall near the bridge.
Take me home, and Priestess Gut will brand you so you can join the tribe as well.
Follow me. I'll keep you safe.
I just saved your life. Show some gratitude.
She's got all kinds of booyahg. Sickly tastin' stuff - might make your limbs grow back, but it's as sour as a bugbear's widdle.
The lady that sent me here's the cruellest drow I ever met. You could learn a thing or two from her.
Too late for that, worgmeat. My tribe's comin'.
Good to be free again, gotta say.
No drow would sully themselves in a goblin tribe. That's madness.
Then you can come to our camp an' learn all about the Absolute. Deal?
I tell ya anyfing, they'll toss me back in the pit!
Somebody 'elp me!
Leave.
Oi! Don't leave yer pal Sazza behind! I can't follow yer fancy booyahg.

EditorData.NodeContext: urgent - being escorted by the player and they were going to use a teleport which would have left her behind - booyagh is pronounced

Text.Value: Do I look like I'm scared of goblins? I'll smash 'em, like the last lot.
They can try, but they won't be the first goblins I've killed today.
Nobody sent me.
Take this. It's everything I've got. I won't try an' get ya killed again, promise.
Goddess.
What's in your priestess' chapel?
Help me escape, an' I'll tell my mates to leave ya alone.
Slow down. I have questions for you.
Get me outta 'ere, an' I'll introduce you to my tribe. You'd like 'em.
You won't regret it, promise.
Follow me. I'll keep you safe.
It's too late to make friends, worgmeat. My tribe's comin'.
Bad news for me. Good news for the spiders.
They're gonna burn this pretty camp for the glory of the Absolute and 'ang ya by yer guts.
Priestess Gut will give a little under-dweller like you all the blessings of the Absolute.
Fascinating. It sounds like nonsense, but I'm intrigued nevertheless.
It's a deal, signed and struck.
Leave.
Let her go.
Don't worry, I'll be gone before the killing starts.
Door's open, I see. 'Elp me escape, an' I'll introduce ya to my tribe, all friendly-like.
Another drow - she's one of my best mates. Thought you might work for her.
Bloody tiefs everywhere. We movin' or wot?
Wot do ya say? We 'ave a deal?
The power of the Absolute, of course! Priestess Gut will tell you all about Her and get ya branded.
Help me escape, an' I'll tell my tribe to leave ya alone when they murder this place.

Synopsis:
If the player saves the goblin captive from being killed, the goblin will try to convince the player to free them and then meet the player later in the goblin camp. Note from Swen on this dialogue: ''I also want a different emotion in there. This goblin is negotiating with me. Think a terrorist that is locked up and who is offering their interrogators an option to save their lives if they free her.
It'll be quite the intense conversation.''
